            <p>
                 Name: Papikondalu <br>

Location: Telangana, India <br>

Description: Papikondalu, also known as Papi Hills, is a picturesque hill range situated on the banks of the Godavari River in Telangana. The region is known for its lush greenery, serene landscapes, and the scenic beauty of the Godavari river flowing through the hills. <br>

Best Time to Visit: October to March. During this period, the weather is pleasant, and the river is full, making it the ideal time to enjoy the beauty of Papikondalu. <br>

Ideal Vacation Duration: 1-2 days. A short trip is sufficient to explore the major attractions and enjoy a boat ride on the Godavari river. <br>

Average Expenses: Starting from ₹6,000 (1-2 days/1 night). The expenses may vary based on accommodation, travel, and activities chosen. <br>
Things to Do: <br>

Boat Cruise: Embark on a relaxing boat cruise on the Godavari river, offering panoramic views of the surrounding hills and forests. <br>

Nature Walks: Take leisurely walks amidst the natural beauty of Papikondalu, enjoying the tranquility and fresh air. <br>

Photography: Capture the stunning landscapes and scenic beauty of the region through your camera lens. <br>

Experience Local Cuisine: Relish the authentic Telugu cuisine and local delicacies of the region. <br>
